6. Stan Lee
Every company concentrates on "top talent" for the people who do actual work, but there is so rarely a focus on a management structure that enables top talent to succeed. Management requires talent, too. So few companies recognize that. You can have the greatest programmers in the world, but unless there is someone who can properly direct them, nothing of substance will be accomplished.
1-6. Don't hire Matt Millen.
